[thinking] **Considering schema collisions**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about what happens if I run the same binary repeatedly with a stale database. If the container persists, the schema from the native compile could potentially collide when rerunning. It seems better to use a test method that generates a new schema each time it runs. For an existing test, I don't need a static final, but rather a method-local schema that includes a timestamp. Maybe editing the schema out is the way to go.
